1 pint fresh button/Crimini mushrooms (or other varieties that you
like)
1 tablespoon olive oil
6 slices of bacon, cut into bite-sized pieces
1/2 cup of sliced onions
1/2 cup of champagne, asti spumanti, or other sparkling white wine
salt and pepper to taste

1.  Saute bacon pieces in a skillet until lightly browned.  Drain and
set aside, reserving 1 teaspoon of bacon drippings.

2.  Put reserved bacon drippings in skillet with olive oil over medium
heat.

3.  Add sliced onions and &quot;sweat&quot; them for several minutes (do not
allow them to brown, however).

4.  Add mushrooms and toss.  Cook mixture for several minutes, until
mushrooms begin to soften noticeably.

5.  Add wine, stir,  and cook for 1 minute.  Taste.

6.  Add salt and pepper, as required.

Turn dish out into a serving bowl and sprinkle with chopped parsley
garnish.

Serves 4 ordinary people, or just me by myself.

